ism and the articulation of national identity.Includes:The Arab past (the interpretation and reinvention of tradition and myth-making)The clash between Arab and Turkish cultural nationalism in the 19th and early 20th centuryReadings of canonical treatises on Arab cultural nationalismA study of the major ideological trends linking language to territorial nationalismA research agenda for the study of language and nationalism in the Arab contextThis is the first full-scale study of this important topic and will be of interest to students of nationalism, Arab and comparative politics, Arabic Studies, history, cultural studies and sociolinguistics."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aIslamic Studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074861707440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447293740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474472937423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474472937/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK